  "faq_q1": "How does automatic payout work?",
  "faq_a1": "When a disruption is confirmed (DCS ≥ 70) and your income drops >40%, EarnIQ automatically creates a claim and sends money to your UPI within 90 seconds. No forms needed.",
  "faq_q2": "Why was my claim rejected?",
  "faq_a2": "Claims are rejected if: (1) DCS was below 70 in your zone, (2) your GPS showed you weren't in the disruption zone, or (3) the fraud engine detected anomalies. You can appeal once per month.",
  "faq_q3": "When is my premium deducted?",
  "faq_a3": "Every Monday at 6 AM via Razorpay auto-debit. You'll get a notification Sunday night with your next week's premium amount.",
  "faq_q4": "What is DCS score?",
  "faq_a4": "Disruption Confidence Score (0–100) measures how severe a disruption is in your zone using weather, AQI, traffic, government alerts, and worker activity data. Claims trigger at DCS ≥ 70.",
  "faq_q5": "What is NOT covered?",
  "faq_a5": "EarnIQ only covers income loss. Health issues, accidents, vehicle damage, and personal emergencies are NOT covered.",
  "faq_q6": "How do I appeal a rejected claim?",
  "faq_a6": "Go to Claims → select the rejected claim → tap Appeal. Submit your delivery app screenshot and GPS history. Human review within 24 hours.",
